  "prompt": "What are alternate sayings to \"two peas in a pod\"?",
  "response": "\"Two peas in a pod\" is an idiom used to describe two people who are very similar or closely related in behavior, appearance, or ideas. Here are some alternate sayings that convey a similar meaning:\n\n1. **Birds of a feather**: This phrase comes from the saying \"Birds of a feather flock together,\" meaning that people with similar interests or characteristics tend to associate with one another.\n\n2. **Cut from the same cloth**: This expression suggests that two people share the same characteristics or qualities, implying that they are alike in a fundamental way.\n\n3. **Like father, like son**: This saying is often used to point out the similarities between a parent and their child, especially a father and son.\n\n4. **Kindred spirits**: This term refers to people who are very similar in character, nature, or outlook.\n\n5. **Mirror images**: This phrase can be used to describe two people who are extremely similar in appearance or behavior, as if one were the reflection of the other.\n\n6. **Carbon copies**: This expression is used to describe two people or things that are exactly alike, as if one were an exact duplicate of the other.\n\n7. **In lockstep**: This phrase implies that two people or things are moving or acting in complete synchronization or agreement with each other.\n\n8. **On the same wavelength**: This saying suggests that two people think alike or have a mutual understanding, often used when they agree or communicate very well.\n\n9. **Joined at the hip**: This informal saying is used to describe two people who are always together and seem to share everything.\n\n10. **Like twins/two of a kind**: Although \"twins\" literally refers to siblings born at the same time, it can also be used metaphorically to describe two people who are very similar.\n\nEach of these phrases can be used in different contexts to emphasize the similarity or close relationship between two individuals or entities.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
